Package: wheredd
Title: Access Forest Carbon Project Boundary Data
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("First", "Last", , "first.last@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides streamlined access to forest carbon offset project
    boundary data from the Akshata, et al. (2024) forest carbon boundaries
    dataset (<https://zenodo.org/records/11459391>), converted to parquet by
    Alex Logan and hosted on Source Cooperative
    (<https://source.coop/cecil/forest-carbon-boundaries>). Creates a local
    DuckDB database with validated, cleaned project geometries from REDD+
    (Reducing Emissions from Deforestation and Forest Degradation) and other
    carbon offset projects worldwide. Enables spatial queries and filtering by
    location, registry, or project attributes. Focuses on data accessâ€”analytical
    functionality is left to R's spatial and data analysis ecosystem (sf,
    dplyr, terra, etc.).
